    <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-10 items-center">
      <p class="text-gray-600 leading-relaxed">ALO – Assistance for the Landless Organization is a non-profit organization dedicated to empowering the most disadvantaged and marginalized communities, with a special focus on indigenous and ultra-poor populations. The organization was founded in response to the devastating floods of 1995 in the Naogaon district of Bangladesh, with a mission to enhance food security and promote sustainable income generation for affected communities.
The initiative formally began on March 20, 1996, when a group of young, committed activists held a general meeting and resolved to establish an organization dedicated to ensuring equal rights for all and fostering long-term development. Their vision was to build a peaceful society free from hunger and poverty. To formalize its operations, ALO was officially registered on March 25, 1999, under the Social Services Department of the Government of the People's Republic of Bangladesh.
In its continuous journey,</p>
